article.description: Devanei Hampton scored 19 points off the bench and grabbed nine rebounds to lead California over Florida 88-60 Friday night in the opening game of the Timeout for HIV/AIDS Tip-off Classic.
article.headline: Cal uses fast start to run over Florida in Tip-off Classic
article.linkText: Cal uses fast start to run over Florida in Tip-off Classic
article.story:
MALIBU, Calif. (AP) -- Devanei Hampton scored 19 points off the
bench and grabbed nine rebounds to lead California (No. 19 ESPN/USA Today, No. 18 AP) over
Florida 88-60 Friday night in the opening game of the Timeout for
HIV/AIDS Tip-off Classic.

Ashley Walker added 17 points and eight rebounds, while Alexis
Gray-Lawson had 13 points for the Golden Bears (2-0).

Marshae Dotson had 14 points and five rebounds for the Gators
(1-2), while Sha Brooks added 11 points and four rebounds.

Cal went on an 11-0 run to take a 20-10 lead with 10:21
remaining in the half on a jumper by Gray-Lawson. The Bears led by
as many as 25 points in the opening period before holding a 48-27
halftime lead.

The Bears' led by 30 points, their biggest lead of the night,
with 37 seconds left in the game.

Florida led only once in the game when a three-pointer by Kim
Dye put the Gators up by three early in the first half.

Cal shot 64.9 percent from the field as it held Florida to 32.3
percent.
